// ============================================================
//  FallGuard — ESP32 Fall Detector (50 Hz / 4 s / 200-sample window)
//  Fixes applied:
//    FIX 1  DLPF configured at 44 Hz (was unset / default undefined)
//    FIX 3  Model constants from firmware_constants.h (no manual copy-paste)
//    FIX 4  Circular buffer overread corrected in quantization loop
//    FIX 5  reset_voting() added to STATE_COOLDOWN and STATE_POST_SUPPRESS
//    FIX 6  Complementary filter replaces accelerometer-only pitch estimate
//    FIX 7  Orientation check uses Euclidean distance over pitch AND roll
//    FIX 8  User calibration adjusts MEANS_RUNTIME at startup
//    FIX 9  Telegram Bot push notification sent to iPhone on fall alarm
//    FIX 10 MPU6050 range set to ±16g / ±2000°/s to match SisFall dataset
//    FIX 11 Library output scaled to correct physical units (g / °/s)
//    FIX 12 Removed duplicate WINDOW_SIZE/N_CHANNELS (now in firmware_constants.h)
//    FIX 13 Diagnostic prints for MPU scale + quantization chain
//    FIX 14 Slow fall detection — second path for falls without impact spike
//           (faint, weakness collapse, sliding fall) using orientation change
//           relative to continuously updated upright reference
//
//  Required files in the same Arduino project folder:
//    fall_model.h          — generated by train03.py (model binary)
//    firmware_constants.h  — generated by train03.py (quantization + scaler constants)
//
//  Required Arduino libraries (install via Library Manager):
//    MPU6050_light
//    TensorFlowLite_ESP32
//    WiFi       (built-in ESP32 core — no install needed)
//    HTTPClient (built-in ESP32 core — no install needed)
// ============================================================

